---
alwaysApply: true
---

Execute the `tox` command to run the tests. It runs all `pytest` tests in
`tests/**/test_*.py` files and all `doctest` examples in source code docstrings.
Do _not_ change directories before running `tox`, it is unnecessary and will be
blocked. Only commands `tox`, `head` and `tail` are allowed.

All functionality should have `doctest` examples demonstrating expected use and
`pytest` tests verifying any additional cases. Focus on readability,
conciseness, and organization when writing tests — prefer quality over quantity.

Ensure you run the test suite with `tox` after making changes and resolve any
failures.
